</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   TOKYO (AP) -- Japanese stocks rose in trading Tuesday following gains on Wall
Street. The Nikkei rose 255.52 points to 15,983.01 in early trading. In New
York, the Nasdaq rose 103.99 to 3,766.99 on Monday after dropping more than 10
percent last week. The Dow gained 10.81 to 10,521.98.
