<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Ambassador's Home Bombed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) -- A bomb exploded Tuesday at the home of
the ambassador of the Philippines in central Jakarta, witnesses
said. At least one person was killed and several injured.
</P>
<P>
   The blast happened at about 12:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Details were sketchy. However, witnesses and police at the scene
said the bomb appeared to have been hidden in a car parked outside
the home near several government offices as well as homes of other
foreign diplomats and senior government officials.
</P>
<P>
   The ambassador's home was severely damaged.
</P>
<P>
   It was not immediately clear who was in the home at the time or
if Ambassador Leonides Caday or other diplomatic staff were among
those killed or hurt.
</P>
<P>
   Office workers ran from their buildings nearby immediately after
the powerful blast, which shook the downtown area.
</P>
<P>
   No further details were immediately available.
</P>
</TEXT>
