<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Red Sox 8, Mariners 5  </HEADLINE>
By JIM COUR
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE (AP) -- Jason Varitek hit a three-run homer in the eighth
inning as the Boston Red Sox rallied to beat the Seattle Mariners
8-5 Monday night.
</P>
<P>
   Trailing 5-4, the Red Sox got singles from Scott Hatteberg and
Mike Lansing off Jose Mesa (3-6) to put runners at the corners with
two outs. Closer Kazuhiro Sasaki came in and allowed an RBI single
to Trot Nixon.
</P>
<P>
   Varitek, a former Mariners' top draft choice, then hit a drive
into the right-field bleachers for his eighth homer. It was
Sasaki's third blown save in 28 opportunities and first since June
14, a stretch of 15 consecutive successful saves.
</P>
<P>
   Rich Garces (6-0) pitched a scoreless seventh to get the
victory. Hipolito Pichardo, who struck out in the ninth, pitched
two innings for his first save.
</P>
<P>
   The Mariners had only three hits off six Boston pitchers,
including two by Rickey Henderson and a grand slam by Jay Buhner in
the first inning.
</P>
<P>
   Buhner and Henderson are the two Mariners who will lose the most
playing time because of the arrival of Al Martin in Monday's trade
with San Diego. Martin will back up Henderson in left field and
Buhner in right.
</P>
<P>
   Buhner's ninth career grand slam came after Ramon Martinez
walked Henderson, Alex Rodriguez and Edgar Martinez.
</P>
<P>
   Henderson, baseball's career stolen base leader, had three
steals and 22 since joining the Mariners on May 17.
</P>
<P>
   The Red Sox came back in the second to score three runs off Paul
Abbott on Nomar Garciaparra's his 16th homer, an error by third
baseman David Bell, and a sacrifice fly by Mike Lansing.
</P>
<P>
   Abbott allowed four runs -- two earned -- and six hits in 5 1-3
innings.
</P>
<P>
   The Mariners made it 5-3 in the bottom of the inning on
Rodriguez's RBI groundout. In the sixth, Lansing had an RBI single.
</P>
<P>
   Martinez allowed five runs, one hit and five walks in one-plus
inning. He has a 46.29 in two starts against Seattle.
</P>
<P>
Notes: The Red Sox placed 2B Jose Offerman on the DL with a
bruised left knee retroactive to July 30. INF Morgan Burkhart was
recalled from Triple-A Pawtucket. The team requested unconditional
release waivers on INF Mike Stanley. ... The Mariners sent IF-OF
John Mabry and minor league pitcher Tom Davey to San Diego. ...
Buhner is 4-for-7 with two homers, both this season, and a double
in his career against Martinez. ... After Henderson's single in the
second, he had reached base eight consecutive times; two hits and
six walks. ... Henderson stole three bases in a game for the first
time since July 16, 1999, for the Mets at Tampa Bay.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
