<HEADLINE> World's Largest Roller Coaster Opens  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TOKYO (AP) -- An amusement park in western Japan opened the
world's tallest roller coaster Tuesday following a ribbon cutting
ceremony attended by the Guinness Book of World Records.
</P>
<P>
   Nagashima Spaland's Steel Dragon 2000 took thrill-seekers on a
1&AMP;frac12; mile course that scales a 320-foot hill, then races down a
68-degree slope, the park said. The ride lasts nearly 4 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   The park is located some 200 miles west of Tokyo.
</P>
