<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-01 12:23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> At the Movies: 'The Tao of Steve'  </HEADLINE>
By DAVID GERMAIN
<TEXT>
<P>
   If you're looking for love, ''The Tao of Steve'' presents a
blithe cinematic how-to, spelling out the do's, don'ts and maybes
for successful courtship.
</P>
<P>
   Captured with great heart and humor, this refreshing romantic
comedy is highlighted by winning performances from Donal Logue as
an overweight, underachieving lady-killer and Greer Goodman as the
woman who spells femme fatale for his lecherous ways.
</P>
<P>
   On its surface, the movie is a fairly predictable
boy-remeets-girl story as Dex (Logue) woos Syd (Goodman), a
forgotten woman from his torrid Casanova-on-campus days in Santa
Fe, N.M., a decade earlier.
</P>
<P>
   What elevates ''The Tao of Steve'' is the smart, mirthful
screenplay co-written by Goodman, her sister and the film's
director, Jenniphr, and their friend Duncan North, whose way with
women was the basis for the script.
</P>
<P>
   The writers insightfully explore dating stereotypes, sexual
posturing and the expectations men and women bring to
relationships. They create a tight little band of romance warriors,
with the ensemble cast depicting disdainful women, haplessly
heartsick men, couples in bliss and marriages on the brink. A third
Goodman sister, Dana, co-stars as a bartender seduced by Dex.
</P>
<P>
   The most important thing in Dex's life is the steady lineup of
women he manages to bed, despite his girth, his slacker lifestyle
and his propensity to smoke pot for breakfast.
</P>
<P>
   In a nutshell, the tao Dex preaches is the image of the remote,
unfathomable male, a James Dean, a James Bond, the sort who ''never
tries to impress women but always gets the girl.'' The ultimate
progenitor of the tao, in his mind, is the icy cool Steve McQueen.
</P>
<P>
   The tao's three key rules: Eliminate your desire, because a
woman will sense it; display excellence in her presence; then
retreat.
</P>
<P>
   ''The basic rule is, we pursue that which retreats from us,''
Dex instructs a tao protege.
</P>
<P>
   Follow these precepts, Dex lectures, and women will capitulate.
</P>
<P>
   It's a gussied-up variation of the schoolyard
playing-hard-to-get approach. But to a degree, the tao of Steve
articulates the sort of guile the most noble of lovers may have
stooped to, posing as something else for fear a new partner will
find fault with the real person.
</P>
<P>
   The perceptive Syd slices through Dex's facade, shaking him and
the tao to their core with an observation about that greatest of
heartbreakers, Don Juan.
</P>
<P>
   ''Don Giovanni slept with thousands of women because he was
afraid he wouldn't be loved by one,'' Syd tells Dex.
</P>
<P>
   Smitten with Syd, Dex halfheartedly continues to trumpet the tao
of Steve while gradually violating its rules. He is unable to
eliminate his desire, telling Syd flat out that he's falling in
love with her. Dex does do excellent things in her presence, though
not the calculated actions the tao requires but gestures from his
ordinary life, such as an endearing encounter with children he
teaches as a part-time kindergarten instructor.
</P>
<P>
   And in the end, it is Syd who retreats and Dex who must decide
whether to pursue or lapse back into wanton ways.
</P>
<P>
   ''I've been trying to turn you into me,'' Dex tells one of his
tao disciples, ''and I'm not even sure I want to be me anymore.''
</P>
<P>
   Logue received a well-deserved special acting award for ''The
Tao of Steve'' at last winter's Sundance Film Festival. The movie
gave Logue his first chance to carry a film after years of smaller
parts in ''The Patriot,'' ''Runaway Bride'' and ''Blade.''
</P>
<P>
   Besides proving Logue can handle a lead role, ''The Tao of
Steve'' marks an excellent filmmaking debut for Jenniphr and Greer
Goodman, who plan to collaborate on future movies. Look forward to
the next chapter in the Goodmans' tao.
</P>
<P>
   ''The Tao of Steve,'' released by Sony Pictures Classics, runs
90 minutes and is rated R for language and some drug use.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   Motion Picture Association of America rating definitions:
</P>
<P>
   G -- General audiences. All ages admitted.
</P>
<P>
   PG -- Parental guidance suggested. Some material may not be
suitable for children.
</P>
<P>
   PG-13 -- Special parental guidance strongly suggested for
children under 13. Some material may be inappropriate for young
children.
</P>
<P>
   R -- Restricted. Under 17 requires accompanying parent or adult
guardian.
</P>
<P>
   NC-17 -- No one under 17 admitted.
</P>
</TEXT>
