<HEADLINE> Council 82 approves new contract  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) - The pared-down membership of Council 82 has
approved a new contract.
</P>
<P>
   The pact calls for salary increases of 13 percent over a
four-year period retroactive to April 1, 1999, when the union's old
contract expired. It also provides members with a $500 bonus.
</P>
<P>
   Council 82 represents about 780 supervisory personnel in the
state Department of Correctional Services, the State University of
New York, the state Department of Environmental Conservation and
other state agencies.
</P>
