<HEADLINE> Jagger's Finances To Be Revealed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Mick Jagger got no satisfaction in family court
Tuesday when his request to be exempted from revealing his finances
in a child custody case was denied.
</P>
<P>
   Quoting a line from the movie ''Jerry McGuire,'' a hearing
examiner told Jagger ''Show me the money,'' and ordered him to
produce a net worth statement.
</P>
<P>
   The 56-year-old Rolling Stone had been directed two months ago
to pay temporary child support of $10,000 a month to Luciana Morad,
29, the mother of 14-month-old Lucas.
</P>
<P>
   New York law requires that a child support order be based on the
parents' ability to pay, as well as on the child's needs. The
hearing examiner said he couldn't file a child support order
without knowing Jagger's income and net worth.
</P>
