<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 'Survivor' Rules Prime Time  </HEADLINE>
By FRAZIER MOORE
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- An island, a house and the seat across from
Regis: Those are the places that most viewers have their eyes on
this summer.
</P>
<P>
   CBS's ''Survivor'' remained the top-rated prime-time show last
week, according to Nielsen Media Research figures released Tuesday.
About 27 million viewers watched college student Jenna get voted
off the island.
</P>
<P>
   Next-ranked were the Sunday, Thursday and Tuesday editions of
ABC's Regis Philbin-hosted game show, ''Who Wants to Be a
Millionaire.''
</P>
<P>
   Then came CBS's ''Big Brother,'' which landed in fifth place
with its live Wednesday edition airing after ''Survivor.'' The
week's other five installments of this voyeur-vision series didn't
fare as well, ranking 20, 29, 45, 48 and 75.
</P>
<P>
   For the week, ABC and CBS tied, each scoring a 6.6 household
rating and a 12 share, though ABC edged out CBS in average viewers
-- 9.70 million to 9.55 million. NBC had 8.87 million viewers (6.2
rating and 11 share), and Fox had 5.91 million (4.0 rating, 7
share).
</P>
<P>
   UPN had 3.19 million viewers (2.0, 4), the WB had 2.42 million
(1.6, 3) and Pax TV had 1.4 million (1.0, 2).
</P>
<P>
   NBC's ''Nightly News'' won the evening news ratings derby with
9.74 million viewers (7.2 rating, 16 share). ABC's ''World News
Tonight'' had 8.81 million viewers (6.7, 15), while ''The CBS
Evening News'' had 7.75 million viewers (6.0, 13).
</P>
<P>
   A rating point represents 1,008,000 households, or 1 percent of
the nation's estimated 100.8 million TV homes. Share is the
percentage of in-use televisions tuned to a given show.
</P>
<P>
   For the week of July 24-30, the top 10 shows, their networks and
ratings were:
</P>
<P>
   ''Survivor,'' CBS, 16.3; ''Who Wants to Be a Millionaire''
(Sunday), ABC, 15.2; ''Who Wants to Be a Millionaire'' (Thursday),
ABC, 14.8; ''Who Wants to Be a Millionaire'' (Tuesday), ABC, 13.5;
''Big Brother'' (Wednesday), CBS, 10.4; ''The Practice,'' ABC, 9.9;
''Law &AMP; Order'' (Wednesday), NBC, 9.1; ''Everybody Loves Raymond,''
CBS, 8.9; ''Law &AMP; Order'' (Monday), NBC, 8.5; ''Mysterious Ways,''
NBC, 8.4.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: http://www.nielsenmedia.com
</P>
</TEXT>
