<HEADLINE> Bradley sees largest monthly growth of 2000  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WINDSOR LOCKS, Conn. (AP) - Bradley International Airport hosted
645,722 passengers in June, a 26.5 percent increase from a year ago
when 510,650 travelers used the airport.
</P>
<P>
   In the first six months of 2000, nearly 3.6 million passengers
used Bradley, a 20 percent increase over the same period of 1999.
The airport is on pace to serve a record number of travelers this
year, Department of Transportation Commissioner James F. Sullivan
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ''Bradley has established a major domestic airport,'' he said.
''The airport has consistently attracted more than 600,000
travelers a month.''
</P>
<P>
   U.S. Airways had 23.5 percent of the passengers with 151,685.
Delta had 20.5 percent with 132,090 customers.
</P>
</TEXT>
