<HEADLINE> Man indicted for criminally negligent homicide in auto death of police officer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - A Staten Island man involved in a high-speed
police chase that ended in an officer's death, was indicted Tuesday
on charges including criminally negligent homicide.
</P>
<P>
   Officer John Kelly, 31, an eight-year veteran of the force,
pulled over Guido Tritto, 43, for speeding along the Staten Island
Expressway, on July 17. When Kelly got out of his car, Tritto sped
off on his motorcycle. Kelly chased Tritto for more than a mile and
then lost control of his unmarked cruiser, smashing into a
telephone pole.
</P>
<P>
   He was pronounced dead shortly afterward.
</P>
<P>
   Tritto fled the scene and was arrested the following day.
</P>
<P>
   ''Officer Kelly died in the line of duty, doing what he did
best, protecting our city. For so many reasons he is a hero. May
justice be served,'' said Staten Island District Attorney William
L. Murphy.
</P>
<P>
   Tritto is scheduled to be arraigned next week.
</P>
</TEXT>
