<HEADLINE> Infant dies in Atlantic City, but cause is unknown  </HEADLINE>
AP Photo
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTIC CITY, N.J. (AP) - A 2&AMP;frac12;-month-old baby boy died Tuesday
after police were called to his home by an adult who told them he
was not breathing. The cause was unknown.
</P>
<P>
   Elijah Luckett was pronounced dead at the scene at an apartment
on Pacific Avenue by representatives of the Atlantic County Medical
Examiner's office. An autopsy was scheduled for late Tuesday,
according to Sgt. Michael Tullio, a police spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   ''Right now, it's just a sudden death investigation. There's
nothing suspicious that we know of,'' Tullio said. ''Unless the
M.E. finds (signs of) trauma, which we don't have now, it's being
treated as a sudden death.''
</P>
<P>
   There were adults in the building at the time of the 12:30 p.m.
call, Tullio said. It wasn't immediately clear who lived in the
apartment with the child, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
