<HEADLINE> Decomposed body of a man found in Egg Harbor Township woods  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   EGG HARBOR TOWNSHIP, N.J. (AP) - The decomposed body of an
unidentified man was found in woods behind a carpet store,
authorities said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The body was found about 5 p.m. Monday in a wooded area behind
Avalon Tile, Carpet and Flooring, on Fire Road, Atlantic County
Prosecutor Jeffrey Blitz said.
</P>
<P>
   A landscaper who was cutting grass in the area discovered the
body about 25 feet from the building, said Blitz, who labeled the
death suspicious.
</P>
<P>
   An autopsy was scheduled for late Tuesday, but results were not
immediately available. It wasn't known how long the body had been
there or when the man died.
</P>
