<HEADLINE> Rain Delays Tampa Bay's Saunders  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUGUSTA, Ga. (AP) -- Left-hander Tony Saunders' rehabilitation
from a broken bone in his pitching arm was delayed on Tuesday when
his scheduled start for Class-A Charleston was postponed by rain.
</P>
<P>
   Saunders, of the Tampa Bay Devil Rays, has been rescheduled to
pitch in a doubleheader Wednesday against Augusta, his first
appearance in a game in more than a year.
</P>
<P>
   Saunders will start the first game and is slated to pitch two
innings or 45 pitches.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm not disappointed, there's nothing you can do about the
weather,'' Saunders said. ''Someone told me it hasn't rained this
hard here in six months. What can you do?''
</P>
<P>
   The 26-year-old Saunders broke his left humerus on May 26 of
last season at Tropicana Field in a game against the Texas Rangers.
He has been throwing in simulated games since May.
</P>
</TEXT>
