<HEADLINE> Devil Rays 6, Indians 5  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- Gerald Williams hit a two-run single
in the ninth inning to spoil Bob Wickman's Cleveland debut and give
the Tampa Bay Devil Rays their club-record tying sixth straight
win, 6-5 over the Indians on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Wickman came to the Indians last week in a seven-player deal
from Milwaukee. But he couldn't hold a 5-4 lead in his first shot
as closer.
</P>
