whether this Caribbean island could become a major tourism destination for Asian
travelers. At the same time, the flights will help expose the Cuban people to
people and customs from another part of the world, said Kenya Uno, chief
political and economic officer for the Japanese Embassy in Havana. Each of the
four charter flights of Boeing 747 jets owned by Japan Airlines will carry up to
350 passengers.
