news agency reported Tuesday. The federal Environmental Protection Agency
ordered Petrobras to pay the amount over three years for a spill earlier this
month that damaged some 370 acres of a preserved area along the Iguacu River, in
southern Brazil, and killed some of the river's fauna, Estado news agency
reported.
