week's preliminary injunction barred the monument until the court decides
whether it is constitutional. The appeal, filed today on orders from Gov. Frank
O'Bannon, seeks to lift the injunction. It will likely delay for months a
decision on the constitutionality of placing the monument on public land, said
Ken Falk, legal director of the Indiana Civil Liberties Union.
